1
00:00:05,076 --> 00:00:05,944
So late.

2
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:08,179
Maybe a case suddenly popped up.

3
00:00:08,813 --> 00:00:10,148
First Division is busy…

4
00:00:10,215 --> 00:00:11,683
I didn't mean them…

5
00:00:11,749 --> 00:00:12,584
Ms. Kudo!

6
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:13,551
They’re here.

7
00:00:17,689 --> 00:00:18,857
Hello.

8
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:21,192
I'm Kudo from the Violent Crimes Division.

9
00:00:21,259 --> 00:00:22,594
I'm Hyuga, First Division.

10
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,963
I'm Ishizaka. I'll show you the way.
Follow me.

11
00:00:26,931 --> 00:00:29,134
-Hello.
-Thank you.

12
00:00:35,106 --> 00:00:37,242
Why are you coming with First Division?

13
00:00:37,308 --> 00:00:38,543
I'm on time.

14
00:00:39,644 --> 00:00:42,480
It's a joint investigation.
You must get here before them.

15
00:00:42,547 --> 00:00:43,748
It doesn't matter.

16
00:00:43,815 --> 00:00:45,183
Mr. Tagusari…

17
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,285
Those guys aren't a big deal anyway.

18
00:00:49,053 --> 00:00:50,421
Going up.

19
00:00:50,922 --> 00:00:52,891
CRIMINAL IDENTIFICATION POLICE

20
00:00:54,025 --> 00:00:55,260
You can go first.

21
00:00:55,326 --> 00:00:56,861
Doors closing.

22
00:00:58,696 --> 00:01:00,165
They heard you.

23
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:02,967
Tagusari.

24
00:01:03,034 --> 00:01:04,769
You were in charge
of the post-mortem, right?

25
00:01:04,836 --> 00:01:05,670
Yes.

26
00:01:05,737 --> 00:01:07,539
The male victim got in an accident

27
00:01:07,605 --> 00:01:11,075
and died in his apartment
due to an acute blood clot in the brain.

28
00:01:11,643 --> 00:01:15,780
A post claiming the victim had once
driven a high school student to suicide

29
00:01:15,847 --> 00:01:17,415
had gone viral on social media,

30
00:01:17,482 --> 00:01:19,817
so he was using
a forged ID to hide his identity.

31
00:01:20,385 --> 00:01:22,287
So his real name is Jun Okochi?

32
00:01:22,353 --> 00:01:24,255
The person who hit Okochi with their car

33
00:01:24,322 --> 00:01:27,492
was Masaya Nogami, the father
of the deceased high school student.

34
00:01:27,559 --> 00:01:30,695
After being interrogated
at the Aoi Station, he disappeared.

35
00:01:32,931 --> 00:01:35,099
The deceased, Jun Okochi,

36
00:01:35,166 --> 00:01:37,435
was a swimming club coach
at Ryoshin High School

37
00:01:37,502 --> 00:01:38,736
until two years ago.

38
00:01:39,404 --> 00:01:42,440
It's a powerhouse school
that produces Olympic athletes,

39
00:01:42,507 --> 00:01:47,011
and it seems Okochi was extremely strict
in his coaching of the members.

40
00:01:47,078 --> 00:01:49,714
And Nogami’s son was among those members?

41
00:01:49,781 --> 00:01:50,648
Yes.

42
00:01:51,149 --> 00:01:52,116
Two years ago,

43
00:01:52,183 --> 00:01:55,720
Taiki Nogami’s body
was found in the Tsugumi River.

44
00:01:55,787 --> 00:01:56,754
His autopsy record?

45
00:01:56,821 --> 00:02:01,059
He had hyper-inflated lungs
and white froth at the mouth and nose,

46
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:04,028
so it was presumed to be
accidental death by drowning.

47
00:02:04,095 --> 00:02:06,564
We processed it as an accident, back then.

48
00:02:06,631 --> 00:02:08,766
But he was an elite swimmer, right?

49
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:12,003
The weather was bad that day,
and the river was overflowing.

50
00:02:12,837 --> 00:02:15,840
However, now that Okochi’s
harsh coaching has come to light,

51
00:02:16,474 --> 00:02:19,110
it's possible it was not an accident,
but a suicide.

52
00:02:19,177 --> 00:02:23,214
So Nogami fled, afraid people
would find out he hit him on purpose.

53
00:02:23,281 --> 00:02:25,817
Search thoroughly,
and take Nogami into custody.

54
00:02:25,883 --> 00:02:26,851
Yes, sir!

55
00:02:30,655 --> 00:02:32,890
Starting with Nogami’s inner circle?

56
00:02:33,758 --> 00:02:35,560
Probably a waste of time.

57
00:02:36,828 --> 00:02:38,162
He’s likely overseas now.

58
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:41,099
Airports, railways, main highways…

59
00:02:41,165 --> 00:02:43,401
First Division
will check them all to find him.

60
00:02:44,802 --> 00:02:46,304
You should help out too.

61
00:02:47,005 --> 00:02:49,140
Without the body,
what can a medical examiner do?

62
00:02:50,942 --> 00:02:52,076
Mr. Tagusari!

63
00:02:53,778 --> 00:02:56,047
I managed to get in touch
with Nogami’s wife.

64
00:02:57,248 --> 00:02:58,149
Got it.

65
00:03:04,455 --> 00:03:05,323
Makoto.

66
00:03:09,627 --> 00:03:11,362
Nogami’s motive is revenge.

67
00:03:16,968 --> 00:03:18,836
Can you really arrest him?

68
00:03:30,915 --> 00:03:33,518
Have you heard from your husband?

69
00:03:35,653 --> 00:03:37,622
Any idea where he might be?

70
00:03:38,256 --> 00:03:39,324
No…

71
00:03:40,558 --> 00:03:45,129
Even after the accident the other day,
he didn't tell me anything.

72
00:03:48,299 --> 00:03:50,401
Had Taiki always been into swimming?

73
00:03:50,468 --> 00:03:53,171
It was his dream to go to the Olympics.

74
00:03:53,738 --> 00:03:57,375
He even got into Ryoshin High School
on a sports scholarship.

75
00:03:57,875 --> 00:04:01,112
But he ended up ruining his shoulder
from the harsh training.

76
00:04:03,047 --> 00:04:06,017
Even so, he participated
in the tournament relay,

77
00:04:06,617 --> 00:04:10,188
but he felt it was his fault they lost.

78
00:04:27,672 --> 00:04:28,706
What's wrong?

79
00:04:34,579 --> 00:04:37,548
Do you know of any places
your dad might go?

80
00:04:38,883 --> 00:04:39,951
I don't.

81
00:04:41,919 --> 00:04:45,423
Back then, did your brother
ever talk about the swimming club?

82
00:04:46,924 --> 00:04:48,092
No.

83
00:04:50,695 --> 00:04:51,662
Did my dad…

84
00:04:53,631 --> 00:04:55,166
really kill someone?

85
00:05:00,471 --> 00:05:01,439
Probably.

86
00:05:02,373 --> 00:05:04,709
Hey! Mr. Tagusari!

87
00:05:06,944 --> 00:05:09,447
We are still investigating right now.

88
00:05:23,361 --> 00:05:25,563
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here it is.

89
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,932
The swimming club roster
from two years ago.

90
00:05:27,999 --> 00:05:29,033
Thank you.

91
00:05:29,634 --> 00:05:33,337
What happened to Taiki Nogami
was very unfortunate.

92
00:05:33,938 --> 00:05:37,041
I would like to ask about the coach,
Jun Okochi.

93
00:05:38,209 --> 00:05:41,012
My understanding is that
his coaching methods were appropriate.

94
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:46,751
I’m sure it was strict at times,
but it was unavoidable to get results.

95
00:05:46,818 --> 00:05:49,120
The members understood that as well.

96
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:54,559
However, he also felt responsible
and stepped down soon after.

97
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,496
But the school was not at fault.

98
00:05:59,464 --> 00:06:00,398
It was an accident.

99
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,536
Sounds like a textbook cover-up.

100
00:06:05,603 --> 00:06:07,305
Hey, that's rude.

101
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:10,708
I’m sorry.

102
00:06:14,445 --> 00:06:15,913
Yes, this is Kudo.

103
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:18,683
2024 SWIMMING CLUB - TAIKI NOGAMI

104
00:06:18,749 --> 00:06:19,884
Nogami…

105
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,021
Hello.

106
00:06:24,088 --> 00:06:24,922
Hey.

107
00:06:26,224 --> 00:06:27,058
Thank you.

108
00:06:27,124 --> 00:06:28,392
Was Nogami at this shop?

109
00:06:28,459 --> 00:06:29,594
Yes.

110
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:32,630
I showed the staff a photo,
and they're sure it was him.

111
00:06:33,631 --> 00:06:38,302
Apparently,
he was sitting in that seat all morning.

112
00:06:42,473 --> 00:06:44,809
What the hell is he doing?

113
00:06:49,947 --> 00:06:53,184
I've contacted headquarters
and had officers patrol this area.

114
00:06:53,251 --> 00:06:54,485
Understood.

115
00:07:04,562 --> 00:07:05,530
Welcome home.

116
00:07:06,797 --> 00:07:07,932
I'm just here for clothes.

117
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,802
-So you won't be staying here for a while?
-Yes.

118
00:07:16,641 --> 00:07:19,110
Hey, do we have any new toothpaste?

119
00:07:19,176 --> 00:07:20,378
We do.

120
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,888
How are things with Nogami?

121
00:07:31,822 --> 00:07:33,224
Take a look at this.

122
00:07:34,492 --> 00:07:36,594
It's from a coffee shop
Nogami was seen at.

123
00:07:36,661 --> 00:07:37,495
A coffee shop?

124
00:07:37,562 --> 00:07:38,563
Know what it is?

125
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,069
I can't really say just from a photo.

126
00:07:46,537 --> 00:07:48,539
You can't say because it's just a guess?

127
00:07:49,106 --> 00:07:51,576
So this means Nogami is still in Kanagawa?

128
00:07:51,642 --> 00:07:54,579
He's had his revenge,
he should just get out of here.

129
00:08:15,733 --> 00:08:17,101
Taiki, I'll give you this.

130
00:08:17,168 --> 00:08:18,903
VICTORY

131
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:20,137
Oh, wow.

132
00:08:20,204 --> 00:08:21,539
Did you make it, Koki?

133
00:08:22,239 --> 00:08:24,075
The failed attempt goes to you, Dad.

134
00:08:24,141 --> 00:08:25,242
VICTORY

135
00:08:25,309 --> 00:08:27,211
Why do I get the reject?

136
00:08:28,346 --> 00:08:29,246
Taiki.

137
00:08:30,081 --> 00:08:33,951
You have to win the next tournament, okay?

138
00:08:34,885 --> 00:08:35,953
I will.

139
00:08:53,804 --> 00:08:57,642
Nogami had been absent from work
without notice before running away.

140
00:08:57,708 --> 00:09:00,344
No sign of him visiting
Taiki Nogami’s grave either.

141
00:09:00,411 --> 00:09:02,847
Anything from the officers
near the coffee shop?

142
00:09:02,913 --> 00:09:04,148
No reports yet.

143
00:09:05,516 --> 00:09:07,551
Nogami’s credit card has been used!

144
00:09:08,119 --> 00:09:10,254
-Where?
-A little past 7:00 p.m. yesterday.

145
00:09:10,321 --> 00:09:13,324
He bought a suit
at a shopping mall in the prefecture.

146
00:09:13,391 --> 00:09:16,327
-A suit?
-Planning to blend into the rush hour?

147
00:09:16,394 --> 00:09:18,029
Check nearby security cameras.

148
00:09:18,095 --> 00:09:19,296
Yes, sir!

149
00:09:21,999 --> 00:09:24,268
A heart attack, huh?

150
00:09:25,136 --> 00:09:27,438
There’s no external trauma,

151
00:09:27,505 --> 00:09:30,241
so it doesn't seem like
there's any foul play.

152
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:33,811
Where was this body found?

153
00:09:34,578 --> 00:09:38,549
He collapsed yesterday
while fishing in the river.

154
00:09:40,584 --> 00:09:41,852
Send this to forensics.

155
00:09:41,919 --> 00:09:42,753
Okay.

156
00:09:49,126 --> 00:09:50,327
You also have an autopsy?

157
00:09:50,828 --> 00:09:51,696
Found anything?

158
00:09:52,263 --> 00:09:54,231
I have no clue at all.

159
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,634
Want a drink?

160
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:02,606
First a coffee shop, now a shopping mall.

161
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:06,744
He drank coffee for an hour,
then disguised himself in a suit.

162
00:10:06,811 --> 00:10:09,080
You would usually disguise yourself first.

163
00:10:09,146 --> 00:10:11,115
His moves are too unpredictable.

164
00:10:11,182 --> 00:10:13,117
The locations are far apart too.

165
00:10:14,051 --> 00:10:16,487
What is Nogami even thinking?

166
00:10:17,154 --> 00:10:20,024
He risked detection, moving around,

167
00:10:20,091 --> 00:10:23,127
and even used a credit card
that leaves a trail.

168
00:10:25,696 --> 00:10:27,531
Does he have some purpose?

169
00:10:31,268 --> 00:10:32,737
I'll head out for a bit.

170
00:10:33,537 --> 00:10:35,106
To Haruko’s place again?

171
00:10:41,178 --> 00:10:43,347
A family registry

172
00:10:44,415 --> 00:10:45,583
and stamp.

173
00:10:45,649 --> 00:10:48,185
How much would they be worth?

174
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,721
You again?

175
00:10:50,788 --> 00:10:52,523
I'm leaving!

176
00:11:05,469 --> 00:11:07,004
This man again?

177
00:11:07,071 --> 00:11:08,939
Where did you get the info on Okochi?

178
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,142
I can't reveal my sources.

179
00:11:13,811 --> 00:11:15,746
Then let me meet your acquaintance.

180
00:11:15,813 --> 00:11:17,681
What do you plan to investigate?

181
00:11:20,985 --> 00:11:24,221
Does Makoto do any cleaning at home?

182
00:11:25,189 --> 00:11:26,290
We have a rotation.

183
00:11:26,857 --> 00:11:29,160
The deal is that if he slacks off,
he'll pay rent.

184
00:11:30,694 --> 00:11:32,429
He would follow the schedule then.

185
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:35,332
He uses my place
like it's his home, though.

186
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:39,403
It has been almost a month now, hasn't it?

187
00:11:40,104 --> 00:11:41,172
Time flies.

188
00:11:42,573 --> 00:11:45,042
His meeting Haruko
for the first time in a while

189
00:11:45,576 --> 00:11:48,546
happened right after he came
to this police station, didn't it?

190
00:11:49,113 --> 00:11:51,549
He was tracking
stolen goods from an assault case,

191
00:11:52,249 --> 00:11:53,784
and found her pawnshop.

192
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,888
You should see her too.

193
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:02,126
Thanks for the meal.

194
00:12:07,064 --> 00:12:11,669
If more time passes like this,
it will only get harder to meet.

195
00:12:13,437 --> 00:12:14,271
This…

196
00:12:14,338 --> 00:12:15,072
RECEIPT

197
00:12:15,139 --> 00:12:16,974
These seasoning prices aren't right.

198
00:12:17,041 --> 00:12:19,877
You have to check the numbers.
Vendors will rip you off!

199
00:12:23,814 --> 00:12:25,316
Fine, I will.

200
00:12:30,454 --> 00:12:31,622
I don't intend to meet her.

201
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:38,529
It's better if she doesn't
get involved with us anymore.

202
00:12:45,836 --> 00:12:46,971
Twenty yen.

203
00:12:47,037 --> 00:12:48,072
Oh, twenty.

204
00:12:49,573 --> 00:12:50,474
Hello.

205
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:53,711
-The results from this morning.
-Thank you.

206
00:13:02,686 --> 00:13:03,854
Do you have a meeting?

207
00:13:04,788 --> 00:13:07,358
We can't track Nogami’s movements at all.

208
00:13:07,424 --> 00:13:10,261
-Should we try going to the racetrack?
-Racetrack?

209
00:13:10,327 --> 00:13:12,496
A desperate Nogami might be there.

210
00:13:12,563 --> 00:13:14,698
You just want to go there yourself.

211
00:13:14,765 --> 00:13:17,034
We’re going to reexamine his inner circle.

212
00:13:17,101 --> 00:13:18,702
What a pain.

213
00:13:19,904 --> 00:13:22,239
Oh, want a ride to headquarters?

214
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:26,110
Before that,
there’s a place I would like to stop by.

215
00:13:30,014 --> 00:13:31,548
Burr marigolds?

216
00:13:32,249 --> 00:13:35,319
Their seeds were attached
to the body found this morning.

217
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,389
Burr marigolds grow in vacant lots.

218
00:13:38,455 --> 00:13:41,225
They are so-called "hitchhiker" plants.

219
00:13:42,092 --> 00:13:44,862
Normally, the seeds
are dispersed in autumn.

220
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:48,132
So they remained until this time of year.

221
00:13:48,832 --> 00:13:51,335
Have the science lesson somewhere else.

222
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:54,638
What about those seeds?

223
00:13:55,706 --> 00:13:58,242
The same seeds were at
the coffee shop where Nogami was.

224
00:13:59,343 --> 00:14:01,879
So Nogami is hiding there?

225
00:14:01,946 --> 00:14:03,147
I don't know.

226
00:14:03,213 --> 00:14:04,148
However,

227
00:14:04,214 --> 00:14:08,852
the body this morning was found
on the bank of the Tsugumi River.

228
00:14:20,731 --> 00:14:23,600
People don't often come here.
Perhaps that's why the seeds remain.

229
00:14:24,835 --> 00:14:26,437
The report from two years ago

230
00:14:26,503 --> 00:14:29,039
said Taiki Nogami's body
was discovered around here.

231
00:14:31,075 --> 00:14:32,309
It must have been over there.

232
00:14:46,457 --> 00:14:47,558
What are you doing?

233
00:14:53,864 --> 00:14:56,300
I was washing away
the things I don't need.

234
00:14:58,535 --> 00:14:59,803
Things you don't need?

235
00:15:01,872 --> 00:15:02,740
A long time ago,

236
00:15:04,808 --> 00:15:06,510
my dad told me,

237
00:15:08,779 --> 00:15:12,049
if you have worries or pains,
just wash them away in the river.

238
00:15:13,384 --> 00:15:18,122
By the time they reach the sea,
their weight will have lessened.

239
00:15:26,697 --> 00:15:30,367
Did Taiki often come here with you?

240
00:15:32,770 --> 00:15:35,105
He often washed away nerves
before a match.

241
00:15:36,206 --> 00:15:38,008
I also made charms

242
00:15:38,842 --> 00:15:42,046
and gave them to him and my dad.

243
00:15:44,281 --> 00:15:45,215
That day,

244
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:47,951
my brother's charm

245
00:15:50,687 --> 00:15:53,390
was on him and washed away somewhere.

246
00:15:55,225 --> 00:15:56,126
And those flowers?

247
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,234
It wasn't me.

248
00:16:07,671 --> 00:16:10,674
So, Nogami was really here.

249
00:16:19,016 --> 00:16:19,883
What happened?

250
00:16:25,956 --> 00:16:27,724
It seems Nogami used a taxi.

251
00:16:28,325 --> 00:16:30,494
We can track his movements
with the records.

252
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,815
What did you come to wash away?

253
00:16:54,952 --> 00:16:57,354
You wash away things
you don't need, right?

254
00:17:02,292 --> 00:17:03,160
Taiki.

255
00:17:05,796 --> 00:17:09,633
In the middle of the final relay,
my brother stopped swimming.

256
00:17:11,268 --> 00:17:14,972
After that,
he didn't practice or do rehab.

257
00:17:15,038 --> 00:17:16,039
In the end…

258
00:17:21,545 --> 00:17:22,779
Taiki…

259
00:17:25,849 --> 00:17:26,917
was weak.

260
00:17:31,622 --> 00:17:32,789
So it's your brother's fault?

261
00:17:54,611 --> 00:17:56,146
-Welcome.
-Excuse me.

262
00:17:56,213 --> 00:17:57,748
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

263
00:17:58,415 --> 00:17:59,483
Goodbye.

264
00:18:03,987 --> 00:18:05,956
Sorry to bother you while you're busy.

265
00:18:10,427 --> 00:18:12,396
He's not easily found, is he?

266
00:18:12,930 --> 00:18:15,032
So he didn't stay here?

267
00:18:15,599 --> 00:18:19,703
However, there's no doubt that Nogami
got out of a taxi in front of this hotel.

268
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:26,843
Ms. Sasaki. The guest has arrived.

269
00:18:27,377 --> 00:18:29,446
I'm sorry. The guests have arrived, so…

270
00:18:30,013 --> 00:18:31,415
Thanks for your cooperation.

271
00:18:31,481 --> 00:18:32,649
Please excuse us.

272
00:18:33,817 --> 00:18:36,186
Sorry to keep you waiting.
Please follow me.

273
00:18:42,593 --> 00:18:46,730
He stayed at a coffee shop for an hour,
bought a suit,

274
00:18:47,497 --> 00:18:50,801
and got out of a taxi in front
of a hotel he didn't even stay at.

275
00:18:52,069 --> 00:18:54,404
I can't read Nogami’s moves.

276
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:58,208
Oh, I'll be right there.

277
00:18:58,275 --> 00:18:59,109
Okay.

278
00:19:02,980 --> 00:19:03,981
Found out something?

279
00:19:04,481 --> 00:19:09,419
The one who gave me information on Okochi
was Taiki Nogami’s classmate.

280
00:19:09,486 --> 00:19:11,688
-Was he in the swimming club too?
-Yes.

281
00:19:11,755 --> 00:19:14,191
For three years. He should know things.

282
00:19:15,993 --> 00:19:16,960
The police?

283
00:19:17,461 --> 00:19:20,297
I'm sorry. I thought
you wouldn't meet him if I told you.

284
00:19:27,671 --> 00:19:30,474
Okochi backed Taiki Nogami
into a corner, didn't he?

285
00:19:30,974 --> 00:19:32,909
And it wasn't just Taiki, right?

286
00:19:33,410 --> 00:19:34,811
When I looked into it a bit,

287
00:19:34,878 --> 00:19:38,649
rumors of Okochi’s
excessive coaching were everywhere.

288
00:19:39,216 --> 00:19:41,818
I heard there were times
he even laid hands on them.

289
00:19:42,653 --> 00:19:45,656
Many members were injured
due to excessive practice too.

290
00:19:46,523 --> 00:19:48,625
Was Taiki Nogami one of them?

291
00:19:49,893 --> 00:19:52,829
He wouldn't let Taiki rest.

292
00:19:53,864 --> 00:19:58,035
Taiki's shoulder injury worsened,
and by the final relay, he…

293
00:19:58,669 --> 00:20:00,237
couldn't swim anymore.

294
00:20:04,241 --> 00:20:05,909
Why did he quit the club?

295
00:20:06,677 --> 00:20:07,511
What?

296
00:20:08,045 --> 00:20:09,546
If it's an injury, he'd heal.

297
00:20:11,848 --> 00:20:13,050
He was forced to quit.

298
00:20:14,151 --> 00:20:15,752
By the advisor, Ms. Chinen.

299
00:20:16,953 --> 00:20:17,954
Chinen?

300
00:20:18,922 --> 00:20:20,490
Even Okochi’s coaching

301
00:20:20,557 --> 00:20:23,193
was all based
on Ms. Chinen's instructions.

302
00:20:24,594 --> 00:20:25,662
She eliminates anyone…

303
00:20:25,729 --> 00:20:26,797
MAIKO CHINEN

304
00:20:26,863 --> 00:20:28,598
…who doesn't produce results.

305
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:32,135
Is that advisor still at the school?

306
00:20:32,202 --> 00:20:33,236
No.

307
00:20:34,037 --> 00:20:37,240
I heard she’s working
as a prep school instructor now.

308
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:41,278
A prep school?

309
00:20:41,345 --> 00:20:45,549
Apparently,
he was sitting in that seat all morning.

310
00:20:46,917 --> 00:20:48,318
MISAWA PREP SCHOOL

311
00:20:48,385 --> 00:20:49,953
A senior in the swimming club

312
00:20:50,454 --> 00:20:52,656
told me Ms. Chinen
is getting married soon.

313
00:20:57,494 --> 00:20:59,529
POLICE DATABASE
TAIKI NOGAMI

314
00:20:59,596 --> 00:21:00,964
ITEMS RECOVERED FROM VICTIM

315
00:21:02,966 --> 00:21:05,335
CONDITION OF SMARTPHONE, STUDENT ID,
WALLET CONTENTS, POINT CARDS

316
00:21:08,438 --> 00:21:10,140
CONDITION OF PATIENT REGISTRATION CARD

317
00:21:10,207 --> 00:21:12,909
YAURA ORTHOPEDIC CLINIC
TAIKI NOGAMI

318
00:21:17,147 --> 00:21:19,816
Mr. Tagusari, where are you?

319
00:21:20,717 --> 00:21:24,755
Nogami’s target
is the advisor, Maiko Chinen.

320
00:21:25,589 --> 00:21:29,059
TANAKA - CHINEN WEDDING RECEPTION

321
00:22:22,112 --> 00:22:24,448
Targeting her at the peak
of her happiness?

322
00:22:28,852 --> 00:22:30,954
As revenge, it's a job well done.

323
00:22:34,491 --> 00:22:36,159
You knew everything, didn't you?

324
00:22:42,632 --> 00:22:47,904
On Taiki's phone,
there was a message he never sent to me.

325
00:22:49,673 --> 00:22:50,774
It said that…

326
00:22:51,541 --> 00:22:55,245
because of Okochi,
he could no longer swim.

327
00:23:00,183 --> 00:23:01,151
I didn't…

328
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:06,389
I didn't notice anything…

329
00:23:09,993 --> 00:23:11,394
So you caused the accident?

330
00:23:11,895 --> 00:23:14,364
That man didn't even come to his funeral.

331
00:23:16,566 --> 00:23:18,101
He abandoned his past

332
00:23:19,603 --> 00:23:22,739
and lived as if Taiki never existed…

333
00:23:26,142 --> 00:23:27,844
I couldn't forgive him.

334
00:23:47,564 --> 00:23:48,732
That hurts, old man.

335
00:23:50,166 --> 00:23:51,768
I'm Taiki's father.

336
00:23:52,569 --> 00:23:53,436
Taiki?

337
00:23:54,037 --> 00:23:55,739
The boy you killed.

338
00:23:55,805 --> 00:23:57,374
Taiki Nogami!

339
00:23:58,909 --> 00:24:00,644
Wait a minute, it wasn't me.

340
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:02,712
That was the advisor, Chinen's fault.

341
00:24:03,446 --> 00:24:04,314
Chinen?

342
00:24:04,881 --> 00:24:08,318
That was when I learned about Chinen.

343
00:24:11,321 --> 00:24:14,558
While I was waiting in front
of Okochi’s house, the police came,

344
00:24:15,992 --> 00:24:18,228
and I found out he had died.

345
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,735
And then you looked into Chinen?

346
00:24:28,805 --> 00:24:29,973
At the coffee shop,

347
00:24:30,607 --> 00:24:33,410
a prep school student
told me about this wedding.

348
00:24:36,446 --> 00:24:37,480
Ladies and gentlemen,

349
00:24:37,547 --> 00:24:42,052
thank you for coming
to the wedding reception today.

350
00:24:42,752 --> 00:24:47,023
Now, the bride and groom,
and their parents

351
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:51,428
will be at the doors
to see the guests off.

352
00:24:52,162 --> 00:24:54,831
We also have a small gift
for guests coming today…

353
00:24:54,898 --> 00:24:56,433
If you want to do it, go ahead.

354
00:24:56,933 --> 00:25:00,103
Once you are ready,
please come to the bride and groom…

355
00:25:00,170 --> 00:25:01,738
Even if I stop you here,

356
00:25:02,839 --> 00:25:04,274
you'll just do it eventually.

357
00:25:04,341 --> 00:25:05,909
Take care when going home.

358
00:25:07,677 --> 00:25:09,312
The police will be here soon.

359
00:25:15,352 --> 00:25:16,386
Please,

360
00:25:17,887 --> 00:25:19,122
let it end with this.

361
00:26:08,438 --> 00:26:09,406
Taiki.

362
00:26:10,573 --> 00:26:11,675
I'm sorry.

363
00:26:17,147 --> 00:26:19,816
VICTORY

364
00:26:19,883 --> 00:26:21,217
I can't take it anymore.

365
00:26:29,993 --> 00:26:31,261
You…

366
00:26:32,529 --> 00:26:34,964
have a happy future waiting for you.

367
00:26:36,666 --> 00:26:37,867
But for that boy,

368
00:26:39,102 --> 00:26:40,804
there is no tomorrow.

369
00:26:42,439 --> 00:26:44,441
Don't you ever forget Taiki!

370
00:26:47,644 --> 00:26:50,447
Don't forget Taiki!

371
00:26:51,347 --> 00:26:53,283
Never forget Taiki Nogami!

372
00:26:53,883 --> 00:26:57,320
Never forget him!

373
00:26:59,956 --> 00:27:01,725
Don't forget him!

374
00:27:13,870 --> 00:27:15,472
Why didn't you wait?

375
00:27:16,873 --> 00:27:18,508
Why did you act on your own?

376
00:27:23,613 --> 00:27:24,781
Would you

377
00:27:26,549 --> 00:27:27,851
be able to endure it?

378
00:27:29,786 --> 00:27:31,087
Hey.

379
00:27:31,688 --> 00:27:32,856
We caught him.

380
00:27:32,922 --> 00:27:33,757
But still!

381
00:27:34,724 --> 00:27:37,060
First Division isn't so idle
as to have time

382
00:27:37,127 --> 00:27:38,862
to bicker with local stations.

383
00:27:42,132 --> 00:27:44,300
I'll give him a stern lecture later.

384
00:27:44,367 --> 00:27:45,201
Okay?

385
00:27:46,603 --> 00:27:47,737
Mr. Tagusari.

386
00:27:48,371 --> 00:27:50,173
He had a weapon. That was dangerous.

387
00:27:51,141 --> 00:27:52,842
Don't do reckless things like that.

388
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:58,081
Mr. Tagusari.

389
00:27:58,648 --> 00:28:00,450
What did you mean earlier?

390
00:28:01,584 --> 00:28:03,319
If he could endure it?

391
00:28:03,386 --> 00:28:05,288
Kudo. That's enough.

392
00:28:07,423 --> 00:28:09,692
If your own family were murdered

393
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:13,263
and the killer was in front of you,
what would you do?

394
00:28:17,901 --> 00:28:19,435
What if they were laughing,

395
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:22,705
without ever having made amends?

396
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,975
Of course, I would arrest them.

397
00:28:26,042 --> 00:28:28,278
Because that is our job.

398
00:28:33,783 --> 00:28:35,552
And what does that solve?

399
00:28:45,962 --> 00:28:48,498
1995, APRIL 26

400
00:28:48,565 --> 00:28:50,033
-Sakutaro!
-Yes?

401
00:28:50,099 --> 00:28:51,234
They're here again.

402
00:28:56,606 --> 00:28:58,074
Dad!

403
00:28:58,141 --> 00:28:59,809
Minoru.

404
00:28:59,876 --> 00:29:02,412
I told you not to come as it's dangerous!

405
00:29:04,647 --> 00:29:06,816
It's boring at home.

406
00:29:06,883 --> 00:29:08,618
Do your homework. Your homework!

407
00:29:09,652 --> 00:29:11,988
Ms. Fumi, still doing
that "bili-bili" thing?

408
00:29:12,555 --> 00:29:13,890
It's "rehabilitation."

409
00:29:13,957 --> 00:29:15,592
I want to ride in one too.

410
00:29:15,658 --> 00:29:17,594
-You can't, that's Ms. Fumi's.
-Mr. Sadao.

411
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:18,828
-Yes.
-Okay.

412
00:29:18,895 --> 00:29:19,729
Here.

413
00:29:19,796 --> 00:29:21,064
Go ahead.

414
00:29:21,764 --> 00:29:22,932
This and…

415
00:29:22,999 --> 00:29:23,833
This…

416
00:29:24,767 --> 00:29:25,602
And this is?

417
00:29:25,668 --> 00:29:26,970
Please cooperate with me.

418
00:29:28,404 --> 00:29:29,639
I know.

419
00:29:29,706 --> 00:29:31,574
-Tell us.
-I have nothing to say.

420
00:29:31,641 --> 00:29:33,476
Let me hear your side.

421
00:29:33,543 --> 00:29:35,011
-Hey!
-I'm busy, go home.

422
00:29:35,078 --> 00:29:35,879
No!

423
00:29:35,945 --> 00:29:38,448
I'll come by again tonight.

424
00:29:57,500 --> 00:30:00,336
It hurts!

425
00:30:07,343 --> 00:30:08,912
Hey, is the ambulance here yet?

426
00:30:08,978 --> 00:30:10,613
Arrival is delayed due to a fire!

427
00:30:13,950 --> 00:30:16,119
-Make way!
-Ambulance coming through!

428
00:30:16,185 --> 00:30:18,021
-Stay back!
-Get back!

429
00:30:19,322 --> 00:30:20,523
Thanks.

430
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:21,724
-It hurts?
-Opening the door.

431
00:30:23,626 --> 00:30:24,661
-Hurry!
-Here he is!

432
00:30:24,727 --> 00:30:26,729
-Here you go.
-Makoto!

433
00:30:28,998 --> 00:30:30,166
Minoru.

434
00:30:42,612 --> 00:30:43,579
Makoto.

435
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:46,516
Did you see the face
of the person who ran away?

436
00:30:47,483 --> 00:30:49,852
I didn't see his face.
But I know who it is.

437
00:30:49,919 --> 00:30:51,054
Do you?

438
00:30:52,255 --> 00:30:54,090
He was arguing with Dad.

439
00:30:54,157 --> 00:30:57,226
He said he would
come by our house again tonight.

440
00:31:00,630 --> 00:31:02,332
1995

441
00:31:26,923 --> 00:31:28,524
Makoto…

442
00:31:32,895 --> 00:31:34,497
Is Minoru okay?

443
00:31:34,564 --> 00:31:36,065
He's in the hospital.

444
00:31:36,666 --> 00:31:38,801
He probably doesn't know yet.

445
00:31:38,868 --> 00:31:39,736
Right.

446
00:31:40,403 --> 00:31:41,504
Detective.

447
00:31:41,571 --> 00:31:43,072
What happened?

448
00:31:43,606 --> 00:31:45,975
I'm sorry to say it at a time like this,

449
00:31:46,042 --> 00:31:49,545
but as it wasn't a robbery,
we are investigating it

450
00:31:50,179 --> 00:31:51,881
as a personal grudge.

451
00:31:52,548 --> 00:31:54,150
Did you catch the killer?

452
00:31:56,319 --> 00:31:58,388
The person who was interviewing Dad.

453
00:32:01,991 --> 00:32:03,493
I looked into it,

454
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:06,596
but it wasn't that person.

455
00:32:06,662 --> 00:32:07,497
What?

456
00:32:07,997 --> 00:32:10,733
But we the police,

457
00:32:12,435 --> 00:32:14,537
will definitely catch the killer.

458
00:32:14,604 --> 00:32:17,540
MS. HARUKO ASHIKAGA

459
00:32:32,021 --> 00:32:33,056
What's wrong?

460
00:32:37,627 --> 00:32:40,496
Where are my mom and dad?

461
00:32:42,165 --> 00:32:44,634
I want to see them.

462
00:32:48,805 --> 00:32:52,075
And now, for the final farewell.

463
00:33:05,555 --> 00:33:06,389
Go on.

464
00:33:07,023 --> 00:33:08,091
Makoto.

465
00:33:13,963 --> 00:33:15,031
Minoru!

466
00:33:16,766 --> 00:33:18,468
Mom!

467
00:33:20,336 --> 00:33:21,971
Dad!

468
00:33:22,905 --> 00:33:24,373
Are you sleeping?

469
00:33:24,874 --> 00:33:25,741
Hey!

470
00:33:27,076 --> 00:33:28,010
Minoru.

471
00:33:29,779 --> 00:33:31,414
Mom and dad…

472
00:33:31,914 --> 00:33:33,182
They died.

473
00:33:38,020 --> 00:33:39,822
They won't move anymore.

474
00:33:40,623 --> 00:33:43,126
We shall now seal the caskets.

475
00:33:52,335 --> 00:33:53,769
It's time to say goodbye.

476
00:34:20,196 --> 00:34:21,397
Dad!

477
00:34:22,098 --> 00:34:23,366
Mom!

478
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:26,936
I'll definitely find the killer!

479
00:34:31,607 --> 00:34:36,846
2026

480
00:34:46,088 --> 00:34:47,290
Go in first.

481
00:34:48,925 --> 00:34:51,327
Don't slack off on cleaning up, okay?

482
00:35:06,375 --> 00:35:07,443
He won't come here.

483
00:35:26,529 --> 00:35:28,798
Your dad stopped for your sake.

484
00:35:29,966 --> 00:35:30,800
What?

485
00:35:32,468 --> 00:35:35,404
Your brother probably
let him off with just Okochi.

486
00:35:45,014 --> 00:35:46,649
The files on Taiki Nogami.

487
00:35:49,051 --> 00:35:50,086
Why do you have them?

488
00:35:50,686 --> 00:35:53,189
After analyzing the stored blood,

489
00:35:53,756 --> 00:35:56,626
prednisolone, an inflammation suppressor,
was detected.

490
00:35:58,394 --> 00:36:00,096
This means that a few days
before his death,

491
00:36:00,162 --> 00:36:02,765
he was undergoing treatment
for his shoulder.

492
00:36:03,599 --> 00:36:05,868
Taiki didn't give up?

493
00:36:06,435 --> 00:36:07,803
I used his registration card

494
00:36:07,870 --> 00:36:10,172
to go to the orthopedic clinic
he was visiting.

495
00:36:12,074 --> 00:36:14,310
He had an appointment
for the day after he died.

496
00:36:15,011 --> 00:36:18,481
Taiki Nogami was enduring harsh rehab…

497
00:36:23,486 --> 00:36:24,654
And, it seems, he said

498
00:36:26,322 --> 00:36:28,057
he wanted to swim once more.

499
00:36:32,962 --> 00:36:33,929
Taiki…

500
00:36:36,799 --> 00:36:38,167
He didn't intend to die?

501
00:36:45,741 --> 00:36:47,109
Your brother

502
00:36:48,844 --> 00:36:50,479
wasn't as weak as you think.

503
00:36:55,751 --> 00:36:57,620
Though that last part is just a guess.

504
00:37:09,832 --> 00:37:12,335
Still, no one knows the truth.

505
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:19,208
Was it your father's love?

506
00:37:20,476 --> 00:37:22,078
Was he a strong brother?

507
00:37:24,780 --> 00:37:26,816
Choose what makes life easier for you.

508
00:37:29,618 --> 00:37:31,153
That is the truth.

509
00:37:39,862 --> 00:37:41,997
MOM

510
00:37:44,900 --> 00:37:46,736
MOM

511
00:37:53,142 --> 00:37:56,379
Mr. Tagusari.
Box up those documents over there.

512
00:37:56,445 --> 00:37:57,713
Sure.

513
00:38:03,219 --> 00:38:05,855
You don't trust First Division?

514
00:38:07,757 --> 00:38:08,858
Not really.

515
00:38:10,793 --> 00:38:12,027
Get along with them.

516
00:38:12,828 --> 00:38:14,363
You'll be collaborating often.

517
00:38:25,641 --> 00:38:26,609
I'm home.

518
00:38:27,343 --> 00:38:28,310
Welcome back.

519
00:39:37,847 --> 00:39:39,215
Get a lot of fish here?

520
00:39:40,816 --> 00:39:43,352
It doesn't matter.
I just like watching the water.

521
00:39:45,855 --> 00:39:47,223
Here's the information fee.

522
00:39:48,557 --> 00:39:51,594
There's no way I can take
money from you, Makoto.

523
00:39:55,598 --> 00:39:56,899
I'll buy you a meal then.

524
00:39:57,433 --> 00:39:58,968
I said it's fine.

525
00:40:05,241 --> 00:40:07,076
Come on, keep me company today.

526
00:40:11,347 --> 00:40:12,381
Mogi!

527
00:40:13,282 --> 00:40:14,583
Haruko?

528
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,155
-Can you make a meal with this fish?
-What?

529
00:40:20,789 --> 00:40:22,358
We're a Chinese restaurant.

530
00:40:22,424 --> 00:40:24,026
Don't be so inflexible.

531
00:40:34,036 --> 00:40:35,037
Minoru?

532
00:40:37,172 --> 00:40:38,240
Have you been well?

533
00:40:44,179 --> 00:40:45,648
When did you come back?

534
00:40:46,615 --> 00:40:48,350
About three years ago, I think.

535
00:40:48,417 --> 00:40:50,486
You should have contacted me!

536
00:40:50,553 --> 00:40:53,489
Before I knew it,
even your number had changed.

537
00:40:54,089 --> 00:40:55,991
I mean, it's all over already.

538
00:40:59,295 --> 00:41:01,330
That incident
from sixteen years ago today.

539
00:41:01,864 --> 00:41:03,966
It was ruled an accident.

540
00:41:05,467 --> 00:41:06,635
Haruko.

541
00:41:07,202 --> 00:41:09,738
Remember what I told you
when I left this place?

542
00:41:10,606 --> 00:41:12,875
The future ahead of us is longer.

543
00:41:14,310 --> 00:41:15,578
Do what you love.

544
00:41:18,881 --> 00:41:21,750
I kept searching for that man
the whole time.

545
00:41:23,419 --> 00:41:27,089
Whenever we met,
we always talked about the case.

546
00:41:29,758 --> 00:41:31,660
I wanted you to finally move forward.

547
00:41:34,096 --> 00:41:37,499
But if you saw me,
you would be forced to remember the case.

548
00:41:38,133 --> 00:41:40,436
-So my contact info…
-Who asked for that?

549
00:41:44,273 --> 00:41:45,441
I wanted…

550
00:41:49,078 --> 00:41:50,913
to see you, Haruko.

551
00:41:59,922 --> 00:42:02,524
The man who was interviewing
our dad is Yuji Tsuda.

552
00:42:03,158 --> 00:42:05,527
A writer, he won
a newcomer award in university.

553
00:42:07,096 --> 00:42:10,866
That day, he said
he would visit again at night.

554
00:42:10,933 --> 00:42:12,001
But…

555
00:42:13,135 --> 00:42:15,971
that man had an alibi, right?

556
00:42:16,538 --> 00:42:17,840
Then why did he vanish?

557
00:42:18,407 --> 00:42:20,776
Right after the incident,
Tsuda disappeared.

558
00:42:21,310 --> 00:42:22,911
He fled because he's the killer?

559
00:42:24,913 --> 00:42:26,281
Sorry, Haruko.

560
00:42:28,050 --> 00:42:32,287
We have been
searching for him ever since that day.

561
00:42:39,995 --> 00:42:40,929
What are you going to do?

562
00:42:43,132 --> 00:42:44,299
About what?

563
00:42:46,568 --> 00:42:47,503
What will you do…

564
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:49,872
if you find Tsuda?

565
00:43:17,299 --> 00:43:18,300
Excuse me.

566
00:43:20,769 --> 00:43:21,804
Minoru.

567
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:23,505
He was brought in this morning.

568
00:43:23,572 --> 00:43:25,307
He didn't have an ID, but said his name.

569
00:43:25,374 --> 00:43:26,475
Is it really Tsuda?

570
00:43:26,542 --> 00:43:28,277
There's no way I would mistake him.

571
00:43:28,944 --> 00:43:29,912
But…

572
00:43:37,953 --> 00:43:39,621
Pancreatic cancer, stage four.

573
00:43:41,523 --> 00:43:43,892
He went into septic shock…

574
00:43:45,961 --> 00:43:47,463
and is now in a coma.

575
00:44:05,013 --> 00:44:06,448
Make no mistake, it was arson and murder.

576
00:44:06,515 --> 00:44:08,517
Is there a reason she didn't run?

577
00:44:08,584 --> 00:44:09,985
We won't be able to get close to Tsuda!

578
00:44:10,052 --> 00:44:11,687
Is there no other way?

579
00:44:11,754 --> 00:44:14,456
-In that case, we'll do it before then.
-What?

580
00:44:14,523 --> 00:44:15,491
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
